data.title: Theatrical agent, Walter Kane and actress, Lynn Bari who were filing for a marriage license, Los Angeles, 1938
data.meta_description: Access to this collection is generously supported by Arcadia funds.Theatrical agent, Walter Kane and actress, Lynn Bari who were filing for a marriage license. Both wear hats and coats and they lean on a counter.This photograph appears with the article, "Lynn Bari, Screen Player, to Become Her Agent's Bride," Los Angeles Times, 7 Dec. 1938: A1.Text from negative sleeve: 15100- Walter Kane. Lynn Bari. Actress. 12/6/38. [Stamped:] Dec 8 1938Handwritten on negative: Walter Kane. Lynn Bari. 12/6/38Text from newspaper caption: Walter Kane, theatrical agent, and Lynn Bari, actress, who have filed notice of their intention to marry.
